# FleetCo production environment — TEMPLATE (ADR-0014 §4, ADR-0013 data tiers).
#
# Copy to a root-owned, chmod 600, gitignored `.env` on the VPS (at
# /opt/fleetco/.env) and replace every placeholder. This file is committed and
# MUST contain only placeholders — NEVER a real secret (CLAUDE.md, ADR-0013).
#
# docker-compose.prod.yml reads this file two ways:
#   - `env_file: .env` injects it into the api + web containers (runtime config).
#   - Compose interpolates ${IMAGE_TAG}, ${POSTGRES_*}, and ${PUBLIC_DOMAIN}
#     from it into the compose file itself (image tags, postgres init, Caddy).
#
# Data-tier legend (ADR-0013), shown per-variable on the comment line above it:
#   [T1] secret — never committed, never logged (the box's disk encryption + OS
#        access control is the trust boundary, ADR-0014 §4).
#   [T2] PII.   [T4] non-sensitive config.
# Tags ride the comment lines (not the value lines) so no annotation can ever
# be parsed into a value.

# === Image tag (Compose interpolation) ======================================
# [T4] The GHCR tag to deploy. CI pushes images tagged by commit SHA (T3); set
# this to that SHA on every deploy (`export IMAGE_TAG=<sha>`). `latest` is only
# a placeholder so `docker compose config` resolves.
IMAGE_TAG=latest

# === Public origin ==========================================================
# [T4] The single public hostname (no scheme). Caddy terminates TLS for it and
# reads it via {$PUBLIC_DOMAIN}; BETTER_AUTH_URL / CORS_ORIGIN /
# NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL below are all https://<this> (ADR-0014 §2 same-origin).
PUBLIC_DOMAIN=app.fleetco.example

# === Runtime mode ===========================================================
# [T4]
NODE_ENV=production
# [T4] Optional (api default: info). One of: fatal error warn info debug trace.
LOG_LEVEL=info
# Do NOT set PORT or HOSTNAME — the api (3001) and web (3000) ports are baked
# into the images, the Caddyfile, and the compose healthchecks.

# === PostgreSQL ==============================================================
# The postgres container's first-run init credentials. These three MUST agree
# with the user:password/database embedded in DATABASE_URL below.
# [T4]
POSTGRES_USER=fleetco
# [T1]
POSTGRES_PASSWORD=REPLACE_WITH_A_STRONG_DB_PASSWORD
# [T4]
POSTGRES_DB=fleetco

# === API datastores =========================================================
# [T1] Carries the DB password (must equal POSTGRES_PASSWORD above). Host is the
# compose service name `postgres`.
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://fleetco:REPLACE_WITH_A_STRONG_DB_PASSWORD@postgres:5432/fleetco?schema=public
# [T4] Host is the compose service name `redis` (no auth at this scale, ADR-0014 §1).
REDIS_URL=redis://redis:6379

# === Auth (better-auth — ADR-0015, ADR-0021) ================================
# [T1] Session-signing secret, >=32 bytes. Generate with: openssl rand -hex 32
BETTER_AUTH_SECRET=REPLACE_WITH_openssl_rand_hex_32_minimum_32_bytes

# === GPS tracker gateway (Traccar — ADR-0042 M5/M6) =========================
# [T1] Machine-ingest key for the Traccar → API position-forward hop, >=32
# chars. Generate with: openssl rand -hex 32. The SAME value is injected into
# the traccar container's forward header (M6 compose config); the ingest route
# answers 503 while this is unset (fails closed). Before the first forward,
# seed the credential-less gateway system user once:
#   pnpm --filter @fleetco/api exec tsx scripts/seed-gateway-user.ts
INGEST_API_KEY=REPLACE_WITH_openssl_rand_hex_32_minimum_32_chars
# [T1] Password for the dedicated low-privilege `traccar` Postgres role that
# owns the separate `traccar` database in the shared postgres container
# (ADR-0042 c3; distinct from POSTGRES_PASSWORD on purpose — the third-party
# gateway never holds the app DB's superuser credential). Generate with:
# openssl rand -hex 32. Compose injects it into the traccar container as
# DATABASE_PASSWORD; the role + database are created once via the idempotent
# snippet in docs/runbook/traccar.md (which reads this same variable).
TRACCAR_DB_PASSWORD=REPLACE_WITH_A_STRONG_TRACCAR_DB_PASSWORD
# [T4] The public API base URL = https://<PUBLIC_DOMAIN> (ADR-0014 §2).
BETTER_AUTH_URL=https://app.fleetco.example
# [T4] Same-origin allowlist = the single public origin (ADR-0014 §2).
CORS_ORIGIN=https://app.fleetco.example

# === Web admin ==============================================================
# [T4] BAKED into the web image at build time (T3 --build-arg; deploy.md step
# 0) — into the SERVER bundle as well as the browser bundle, so this on-box
# line is runtime-inert for the web app and stands as the record of the baked
# origin. Keep it equal to the public origin (ADR-0014 §2 same-origin).
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://app.fleetco.example

# === Admin seed (one-off `db:seed`, ADR-0014 §9 / ADR-0021) =================
# Read only by the one-time seed task to create the first admin user.
# [T2]
ADMIN_EMAIL=admin@fleetco.example
# [T1]
ADMIN_PASSWORD=REPLACE_WITH_THE_FIRST_ADMIN_PASSWORD
# CREATE_USER_PASSWORD (the office-staff/admin creation path, ADR-0028) is passed
# INLINE on the create-user command at run time, never stored here.

# === AI chat agent (DeepSeek — ADR-0043) ====================================
# [T1] when set. The agent's hosted-LLM API key. LEAVE EMPTY TO KEEP THE AGENT
# OFF THE NETWORK: unset means the API binds the no-network MockLlmClient — the
# production kill switch (ADR-0043 c2). Set only after the ADR-0042 deploy
# reaches daily use AND the DeepSeek training opt-out has been requested for
# the account (ADR-0043 c6).
DEEPSEEK_API_KEY=
# [T4] Optional (api default: deepseek-v4-flash). The model name the agent
# requests; the legacy deepseek-chat / deepseek-reasoner names deprecate
# 2026-07-24.
DEEPSEEK_MODEL=deepseek-v4-flash

# === WhatsApp agent channel (Twilio — ADR-0046) ==============================
# ALL optional and EMPTY at the first deploy: while the TWILIO_* group is unset
# the api binds MockWhatsAppSender and the inbound webhook fails closed (503) —
# the channel is OFF (the DEEPSEEK_API_KEY kill-switch idiom). Activation is a
# deliberate post-deploy step owned by docs/runbook/whatsapp-operations.md
# (register the sender, set these five, recreate the api container, provision
# the phone link) — set nothing here on the first pass.
# [T1] Account SID + auth token. The token both verifies inbound
# X-Twilio-Signature headers AND Basic-auths outbound sends — never logged,
# never committed.
TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID=
TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN=
# [T4] The WhatsApp-enabled sender, in Twilio's whatsapp:+<E164> form.
TWILIO_WHATSAPP_FROM=
# [T4] The EXACT public webhook URL registered with Twilio — signature
# verification pins this constant byte-for-byte (scheme, host, path):
# https://<PUBLIC_DOMAIN>/api/v1/whatsapp/inbound
TWILIO_WEBHOOK_URL=
# [T4] The admin web's public base URL for reply deep-links —
# https://<PUBLIC_DOMAIN> on the single-origin deploy (ADR-0014 §2).
WEB_PUBLIC_URL=

# === Reminder delivery (Resend — ADR-0038) ==================================
# The compliance/maintenance reminder digest (daily 01:00 UTC scan) delivers
# ONLY when this group is set; while empty the api binds the no-network
# MockMailer and nothing sends (the DEEPSEEK_API_KEY kill-switch idiom).
# Activation is operator-led: verify a sending domain in Resend (SPF/DKIM/
# DMARC — ADR-0038 c9), then set both and recreate the api container.
# [T1] The Resend API key — never logged, never committed.
RESEND_API_KEY=
# [T4] The sending address on the VERIFIED domain, e.g.
# "FleetCo <reminders@yourdomain.com.np>". Unset falls back to a reserved
# `.example` placeholder that can never deliver — set it with the key.
RESEND_FROM=
# [T2] Optional comma-separated extra recipients added to the ADMIN users'
# emails (a shared inbox, the accountant). Addresses are PII — never logged.
NOTIFICATION_RECIPIENTS=

# === Object storage (Cloudflare R2 — ADR-0039 c7 / ADR-0044 V2) =============
# Required for invoice ISSUE (the PDF is stored at issue time) and for agent
# photo attachments + fleet documents (ADR-0049); while ANY is empty the api
# binds an in-memory mock store and invoice issue() refuses with a clear 422 —
# so the api never reaches R2 until the operator configures it.
#
# SHARED BUCKET (ADR-0014 §6): this is the SAME R2 bucket the nightly backup
# uses (deploy/backup.env's R2_BUCKET) — one bucket for the whole project. The
# app writes under the `invoices/`, `documents/`, and `agent-attachments/`
# key PREFIXES; the backups sit at the bucket ROOT as `fleetco-<date>.sql.gz.age`.
# The backup's 30-day prune is filename-scoped (`--include /fleetco-*.sql.gz.age`)
# so it NEVER deletes an app object — see deploy/backup.sh. If you instead want a
# separate bucket, point this at that bucket and give it its own scoped token.
# From the Cloudflare dashboard: an R2 API token scoped to this bucket.
# [T4] The S3 API endpoint, https://<accountid>.r2.cloudflarestorage.com
R2_ENDPOINT=
# [T1] The R2 API token pair — never logged, never committed. May be the SAME
# token the backup rclone remote uses, or a distinct app-scoped token (a
# distinct token limits blast radius: the app key then cannot read/delete the
# encrypted backups, your disaster-recovery lifeline).
R2_ACCESS_KEY_ID=
R2_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=
# [T4] The bucket name — the SAME value as the backup's R2_BUCKET when sharing.
R2_BUCKET=

# === Invoice supplier identity (ADR-0039 c9) ================================
# Required before issuing a REAL invoice (issue() refuses 422 while the PAN is
# empty). Operator/accountant-verified values only — never fabricated.
# [T3] FleetCo's OWN supplier PAN/VAT number printed on every tax invoice.
INVOICE_SUPPLIER_PAN=
# [T4] The registered business name for the invoice header (api default:
# "FleetCo").
INVOICE_SUPPLIER_NAME=

# === Observability (optional — ADR-0024) ====================================
# [T1] when set (ADR-0014 §4). Leave empty to disable.
SENTRY_DSN=
# [T4] Leave empty to disable.
OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT=

# --- Agent document extraction (ADR-0044 Box B: self-hosted OCR sidecar) ----
# LEAVE EMPTY AT THE FIRST DEPLOY. Set only when the OCR sidecar container is
# up on the box (its own compose service + runbook step, ticket V6+; the
# sidecar needs ~5 GB resident — the VPS sizing note in ADR-0044 Box B).
# Unsetting this is the image-extraction kill switch (the DEEPSEEK_API_KEY
# pattern): chat keeps working, attachments degrade to an honest notice.
AGENT_OCR_URL=
# Defaults to the ADR-0044-pinned model id; self-quantizing from the official
# weights is the recorded production preference.
#AGENT_OCR_MODEL=huggingface.co/sahilchachra/unlimited-ocr-gguf:Q4_K_M
